// TEST: Physics -- Kramers-Moyal: the Generator is the Jet of the Propagator
import ppl as ppl
// ============================================================================
// The deterministic arc fitted d/dt <g> = L g. For STOCHASTIC dynamics the
// generator is read off the CONDITIONAL CUMULANTS of increments:
//     D_n(x) = lim  kappa_n( x(t+tau) - x(t) | x ) / (n! tau)
// -- the Kramers-Moyal expansion IS the moment jet of the transition kernel:
// drift = first cumulant, diffusion = second. And Pawula's theorem is a
// statement about the jet's truncation order: it is 1 (deterministic),
// 2 (diffusion), or INFINITY (jumps) -- nothing in between. The witness is
// the excess kurtosis of increments, kappa_4/kappa_2^2: identically 0 for a
// diffusion, but 3/(rho tau) for a jump process -- DIVERGING as tau -> 0.
// tools/kramers_moyal.ps1 recovers the full state-resolved generator (drift
// field -x, diffusion 0.25) for two processes built to agree exactly through
// order 2.0, and confirms the 3/(rho tau) law: 119.1, 58.9, 22.5, 10.8, 4.9
// measured vs 120.0, 60.0, 24.0, 12.0, 6 predicted as tau doubles.
// Here Blade's formers make the call on 400 embedded center-bin increments
// (tau = 0.01) from each process: kappa_2/tau agrees (same diffusion), and
// kappa_4/kappa_2^2 = 0.14 vs 103.3 -- SEVEN HUNDRED times apart. Two
// processes indistinguishable at order 2 separate at order 4: this is the
// arc's first result that structurally NEEDS the tower above kappa_2.
// ============================================================================
type TimeIdx = Idx<400>
